Troubleshooting Tips
APKTool fails to decompile:

Ensure Java is installed: java -version
Try older APKTool version if current fails
Check APK file integrity with file command
Python import errors:

Verify virtual environment is activated
Reinstall packages: pip install --upgrade jinja2 xmltodict
Check Python path: which python3
XML parsing errors:

Verify AndroidManifest.xml exists in decompiled directory
Check file permissions: ls -la AndroidManifest.xml
Use xmllint to validate XML structure
Report generation fails:

Ensure assessment was run first
Verify JSON results file exists and is valid
Check template syntax in report generator
Conclusion
This lab demonstrated how to conduct automated MASVS security assessments on Android applications. You learned to decompile APK files, analyze security configurations, implement Python-based assessment frameworks, and generate professional security reports. These skills are essential for mobile application security testing and compliance verification. The automated approach enables consistent, repeatable assessments that can be integrated into CI/CD pipelines for continuous security validation.
